sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device will detect the presence of LasL which is a signaling molecule used by P. aeruginosa. This is tied to make HrpR which is needed in the HrpL AND gate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the LasL protein which is used in P. aeruginosa quorum sensing
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: the promoter region for LasL regulator protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for HrpR. This is one of two proteins (HrpS and HrpR) needed for the HrpL AND gate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel
